Contains implementations for all projections in Map Objects Java.

Class Summary
AlbersEqualArea Implements a AlbersEqualArea projection: Conic Equal-Area Meridians are equally spaced radii of the same circles, intersecting parallels at right angles Poles are arcs of circles Presented by Albers in 1805 Used for equal area maps with east west expanse, (United States)
AzimuthalEquidistantGuamObliqueAspect Implements a AzimuthalEquidistantGuamObliqueAspect projection: Azimuthal Distances measured from the center are true.

AzimuthalEquidistantSouthPolarAspect Implements a AzimuthalEquidistantSouthPolarAspect projection: Azimuthal Distances measured from the center are true.

Bonne Implements a Bonne projection: Pseudoconical.
Cassini Implements a Cassini projection: Cylindrical Neither equal area nor conformal Central meridian, each meridian 90 degrees are straight lines.
CylindricalEqualAreaNormalAspect Implements a cylindrical equal area projection (normal aspect): Cylindrical Equal Area Meridians are equally spaced straight lines Parallels are unequally spaced straight lines, closest near the poles, cutting meridians at right angles Presented by Lambert in 1772 Also called Lambert Cylindrical Equal Area Projection if standard parallel is 0.
CylindricalEqualAreaTransverseAspect Implements a cylindrical equal area projection (transverse aspect): Cylindrical Equal Area Central meridian, each meridian 90 degrees from CM, and equator are straight lines.

EnvelopeHorizon represents the boundary of a geodetic projection.
EquidistantConic Implements a EquidistantConic projection for an ellipsoid: Conic Equidistant Neither conformal nor equal-area Parallels are arcs of concentric circles at true spacing Meridians are equally spaced radii of the same circles, intersecting parallels at right angles Scale is true along meridians and along 1 or 2 standard parallels Developed by Ptolemy in 150 AD Used for maps of small countries and for maps of larger areas with east west expanse.
EquidistantCylindrical Implements a EquidistantCylindrical projection for a sphere.
GallCylindrical Implements a GallCylindrical projection for a sphere: Cylindrical Neither conformal nor equal-area Cuts the earth at 45 and -45 latitude thus true to scale at those latitudes.

HotineAzimuthNaturalOrigin Implements a Hotine Oblique Mercator projection for an ellipsoid.

Package com.esri.mo2.cs.proj Description

Contains implementations for all projections in Map Objects Java. Additionally, it contains the GenericProjection and BaseProjection classes from which all projection implementations are ultimately derived.
